आज  आज़ादी  है,  फिर  भी  घर  जाने  की  जल्दी  रहती  है... !!

कभी  होटल  में  जाना  पिज़्ज़ा,  बर्गर  खाना  पसंद  था...

आज  घर  पर  आना  और  माँ  के  हाथ  का  खाना  पसंद  है... !!!

स्कूल  में  जिनके  साथ  झगड़ते  थे,  आज उनको  ही  इंटरनेट और वाट् सप व फेसबुक पे  तलाशते  है... !!

ख़ुशी  किसमे  होतीं है,  ये  पता  अब  चला  है... 
बचपन  क्या  था,  इसका  एहसास  अब  हुआ  है... 

काश  बदल  सकते  हम  ज़िंदगी  के  कुछ  साल..

.काश  जी  सकते  हम,  ज़िंदगी  फिर  एक बार...!!


👘 जब हम अपने शर्ट में हाथ छुपाते थे और लोगों से कहते फिरते थे देखो मैंने अपने हाथ जादू से गायब कर दिए
|🌀🌀

✏जब हमारे पास चार रंगों से लिखने वाली एक पेन हुआ करती थी और हम सभी  बटनों को एक साथ दबाने की कोशिश किया करते थे |❤💚💙💜

👻 जब हम दरवाज़े के पीछे छुपते थे ताकि अगर कोई आये तो उसे डरा सके..👥

🚤🛥जाने कहां खो गई वो बचपन की अमीरी जब पानी में हमारे भी जहाज चला करते थे🛶⛵और आसमान मे हवाई जहाज....

👀जब आँख बंद कर सोने का नाटक करते
थे ताकि कोई हमें गोद में उठा के बिस्तर तक पहुचा दे |


🚲सोचा करते थे की ये चाँद हमारी साइकिल के पीछे पीछे क्यों चल रहा हैं |🌙🚲


🔦💡लाईट के On/Off वाले स्विच को बीच में
अटकाने की कोशिश किया करते थे |


🍏🍎🍉🍑🍈 फल के बीज को इस डर से नहीं खाते थे की कहीं हमारे पेट में पेड़ न उग जाए |


🍰🎂🍧🏆🎉🎁 बर्थडे सिर्फ इसलिए मनाते थे
ताकि ढेर सारे गिफ्ट मिले |

🔆फ्रिज को धीरे से बंद करके ये जानने की कोशिश करते थे की इसकी लाइट कब बंद होती हैं |


🎭  सच , बचपन में सोचते थे कि हम बड़े
क्यों नहीं हो रहे ?


और अब सोचते है हम बड़े क्यों हो गए ?⚡⚡


🎒🎐ये दौलत भी ले लो.. ये शोहरत भी ले लो💕

भले छीन लो मुझसे मेरी जवानी...

वो कागज़ की कश्ती वो बारिश का पानी.. 🌊🌊🌊

एक बात बोलु 
इनकार मत करना
ये *msg* जीतने लोगों को *send* करो
जो इस *msg* को पढेगा
उसको उसका बचपन जरुर याद आयेगा.
क्या पता वो आपकी वजह से अपने बचपन में चला जाए. चाहे कुछ देर के लिए ही सही।
और ये आपकी तरफ से   उसको सबसे अच्छा गिफ्ट हो.... ।

20/09/19, 1:38 pm - Nikhil GT: *Never Joke with an Engineer :* 

Engineers Can Prove Anything For *10 Marks*

Question : *Prove : PAPA = MAMA.*

Medical Doctor : *”Out Of Course”*

Chartered Accountant: *”No Way”*

Barrister: *”Cannot Be Proven”*

Social sciences: *"Not in this world,"*

but…..

Engineer: *It's a Simple Solution*

As we know,

Pressure(P)= Force/Area

i.e.  P = F/A

*∴F = PA ⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅ (i)*

Now, aacording to Newtons 2nd law of Motion,

Force(F) = Mass(M) × Acceleration(A)

*i.e. F =MA ⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅⋅(ii)*

From equation (i) and (ii)

*PA = MA*

Squaring both sides

*(PA)² = (MA)²*

*∴ PAPA = MAMA*

Share if u r proud of ur profession. 
*ENGINEERS ONLY PLEASE*
😎👍😅

Proud to be an ENGINEER

01/11/19, 1:27 pm - Aryan G: JEE: Wake up at 4 am
IIT: Sleep at 4 am

JEE: Namesake phones with no internet access
IIT: Free Wi-fi

JEE: “I missed class today coz of practicals in school. What was taught?”
IIT: “I’m not attending class today. Can you please mark my attendance for me?”

JEE: Study for two years before the D-Day
IIT: Study for two weeks before the exams (Edit: it’s two days before the exams but no intentions of making IITians sound overly carefree)

JEE: Zero social life and extra academics
IIT: Organising events, meeting new people and even celebrities during fests

JEE: Lucky to get to play a sport
IIT: Gymkhana full of courts

JEE: Mom: “How much did you score in this week’s mock test?”
IIT: Mom: “Are you going with your friends to Darjeeling or Manali?”

JEE: Stay hungry when staying up late, studying
IIT: 24X7 available midnight snacks in canteens that close at 3 am and eateries that open at 3 am

JEE: Clustered around the teacher a day before the exam, clarifying doubts
IIT: Clustered around the smart wingmate before the exam, being taught

JEE: I’m the topper of my institute
IIT: I wonder how I used to be a topper back then

JEE: Not allowed to step outside after 10 pm
IIT: Run-throughs of shows tend to go up to 2 am and even 7 am at times




 

JEE: Alarm clocks, textbooks on PDE, AMINES, & solving a 100 problems a day
IIT: Rackets, PDF’s, ANIME and watching a 100 movies a day (you get the hyperbole)

JEE: Learn physics, chemistry and mathematics
IIT: Learn any new skill you wish to

That’s how life goes for the complete time students spend in IITs. In short, it’s very easy to lead a relaxed and fulfilling life at IITs. Consider it your reward after 2-3 years of hard work. You can pursue your future goals and have fun at the same time.

Aim high and keep your feet grounded. And most importantly, have fun and keep rocking!! You’ll soon set the IIT on fire!

09/11/19, 4:23 pm - Riya: 😞Oh God...
09/11/19, 4:23 pm - +91 80581 02623: Well usually I rarely write any posts, but this is something that needs to be said.

In wake of recent circumstances at IIT-D(A first-year computer science girl committed suicide). I want to ask a question to everyone where are we wrong? Well, I am definitely not aware of all the circumstances but I would like to point out a few things which I feel impact the lives of students at IIT Delhi(Some of my personal experiences).

Being a student of Computer Science, well I will say I am not living. There are countless times I just want that I do not wake up the next day. Why? Because the next day I will be having a quiz, a presentation and an assignment. Let me tell you sab is very very difficult. Just because hum kar lete h doesn’t mean ki hum khush h krke ya hum karna chahte h. Nahi hota yaar, lets be real hum kaise karte h? Hum khana skip karte h, ghar p baat nahi karte, sote nahi h aur anything humans do. Kyunki humare paas time nahi h jeene ka.

Our healths are suffering severely, me myself I have fever once a week. Why because of lack of sleep...what i do? Take paracetamol drink red bull and do assignment.

Why are marks not dependant on learnings? I am someone who likes to learn but what happens to me when I fall in this administration’s hands. Well I gave up on learning. Some first year incidents:
Me: Sir its correct, why haven’t you given me marks?
Sir: Because its you!
(I still am clueless ki maine kya kiya)

Just because of all this what happens to students:
People who start doing drugs: Lets be real people who have worked their asses off to get here, who are supposedly the brightest minds of the country doing drugs, addicted to smoking and drinking!!! Guys, it’s not their fault the system has forced them to do so.
People who stop going to classes: Just because class jaake kya hi ukhad lenge seekhne ki koi vaue to hai hi ni. Jab bas ek din phle rat k bhi utne hi marks aayenge why will I go to class?

We are here to learn, to become responsible adults. Please let it be like that. 

I am doing a project and yesterday only I came to know ki 25 ko presentation deni h, I already booked my flights, I went to the prof and told him. He said it so simply that worse you will get an F. Just like that. I worked for the whole semester all in vain!

One of my friends got a very great opportunity(Sen intern at a renowned university). It was a rigorous procedure she had to go through all by herself. Now they denied that we won’t let third years go. Seriously!!! I could be life-defining for her.

Are rules that very important. More important than our lives? More important than our future? What did we do wrong that we live like this? She was a mere 17-year-old, who was forced by circumstances to take a decision.

Dear Administration, parents and society,
Please treat us like humans. We are not robots, we have limitations on what we can do. If we achieve something, appreciate it. Life is hard as it is. Mose of the people I know are depressed. We can’t handle this level of stress. There are so many times we are on a very vulnerable emotional state please be considerate of how you talk to us. It could be that someone might be looking for a very minimal ray of hope in their lives when you thrash us. Just because of the inhuman behaviour and rules of yours someone might be self-harming, someone might be taking depression tablets, someone might be standing just at the corner of the cliff wondering if his life even matters and someone brave enough might even jump.

Two years back, I saved someone standing at the exactly same spot. I am glad I did that. 

Sincere Regards
An Undergrad at a Prestigious Indian Institute 

PS: The purpose of this post is to make people aware of the real circumstances not to defame any institute or any person in general.

-kaashika prajaapat

Statics (chap 2)

F=ma (chap 3)

Oscillations (chap 4, except coupled oscillator section 4.5)

Conservation laws (chap 5)

Central force (only section 7.1 on conservation laws)

Angular momentum part 1 (chap 8)

Angular momentum part 2 (chap 9, upto section 9.3 principal axes)

26/12/19, 6:06 pm - Rishabh PI: 👆Sir Proby Thomas Cautley ( 3 January, 1802- 25 January, 1871) 👆was an outstanding Civil Engineer who pioneered the idea of conceiving and supervising the construction of approx. 175 years old North Ganga Canal system between Hardwar and Kanpur during East India Company rule in India. At the time of completion, it had the greatest discharge of any Irrigation Canal in the world..!! He was an extremely  dedicated and duty-bound person. In other words, he was a Karmyogi in true sense... Approx. 500 km. north Ganga Canal has been in service ever since  it came into existence in 1854, which is a lifeline of the entire western UP and some part of Uttarakhand....!!  Thomason College of Civil Engineering / Roorkee University ( now IIT Roorkee) was 'born' ( established) due to massive construction activities of this historical  Ganga Canal during middle of 19th century and therefore  "She" ( Ganga Canal) is not only the  "mother" of U.P and Uttarakhand Irrigation Departments but also the mother of this great Institution of learning which is my Alma Mater too - UOR/IIT Roorkee... Let's pay our humble tributes to Sir Cautley for his monumental contribution in huge  developmental works  in that part of the country....My salute to this great visionary Civil Engineer....!!

         चरण स्पर्श,                                      
      मैं यहां ठीक हूँ और आशा करता हू                     
    कि आप लोग सब अच्छे से होगे।।                     
    आगे समाचार यह है कि मेरी लुगाई 🙎                
    पुरानी  और बेकार हो गई है ।।                       
    और यहॉ सर्दी अधिक पड रही है ।।                    
     अभी दोस्तो की लुगाइयों से कामचल रहा था              
    लेकिन सर्दी अधिक पडने से वे भी अपनी लुगाई         
    देने मे आना कानी करते है ।।                           
😁                                             
   मेरे लिये एक लुगाई का इंतजाम कर दो ।।             
    😁नई ना ला सको तो बडे भैया की लुगाई भेज दो ।।    
   😁बडे भैया की ना मिले तो मझले भैया की लुगाई                   भेज। दो ।😁सर्दी मे बुरा हाल है                      
   दो भाईयों मे से किसी एक की लुगाई                    
जरूर भेज दो।😁                                     
  दोनों मे से किसी की भी न भेज सको तो।               
 पैसे भेज दो 😁                                       
    मैं यहॉ किराये कि लुगाई ले लूंगा ।।

17/01/20, 3:46 pm - Sarthak Mech.: *ShARE Recruitment test*

*HOW TO APPLY*

You can apply by filling your application below before  Sunday,19th January 2020 by 23:00 IST https://www.share-share.org/recruitment-iitr/

*NEXT STEP*

Enrolment Test – 20th January 2020 at 21:00 IST

Duration: 1 hour

Preparation: Have ready a less than 1 min video with you explaining what it means to you “Do well Do good."

*INSTRUCTIONS*
*For the TEST:*

1.You don’t need any skills/study preparation before the test 
2.The test has 4 part. Analytical Skills (Multiple choice) + Why ShARE (here you will need to upload your video) + case study + multiple choice questions (After watching the video of one of our expert speakers)
3.Make sure you have good internet connect during the exam
4. We recommend you to use head phones to listen to the video 
5. DO NOT take the test on your mobile device but use your laptop or PC.
6. The test will close at 22:00 IST sharp, if you don’t complete the test on time your answers won’t be recorded.

*For The VIDEO:*

1.The video should be less than a minute
2. Ensure good video and audio quality. Avoid HD quality since the clip may take more time to upload, whereas the time is limited.
3. Answer the question what it means to you Do well Do good.

Thank you again for your interest in ShARE. We wish you the very best of luck !!

17/01/20, 8:09 pm - Tanmay GT: Greetings from Team E-Summit 2020 IIT Roorkee!

Entrepreneurship Cell, IIT Roorkee is organizing its annual flagship event- E-Summit 2020 on 1-2 February. It is a networking hub for corporates, professionals, students, and budding entrepreneurs from all across the nation. We aspire to provide them with the best possible experience, opportunities, and an avenue to enrich themselves with knowledge about the entrepreneurial world. With the theme “Disruption Dilemma,” we aim to create an impact and keep on innovating. Join us as we try to inspire and prepare the next wave of Indian Entrepreneurs who know how to create an effect and keep on innovating!
E-Summit witnesses the presence of the top-notch personalities from the industrial, corporate, and entrepreneurial sectors and engages over 10000 students, 50 startups, and 15 Venture Capitalists from across regions in Asia.
The major attractions in E-Summit 2020 edition include:

*Leadership Series* : Leadership series is a live speaker series; it is an excellent platform for entrepreneurship enthusiasts to learn from the best in the industry. 
*Conclaves*:This year we would be having three conclaves:
1. *Product Management Conclave*: targeting Product Management enthusiasts and the role of PM in product-based startups. The event will consist of speakers who will deliver guest lectures and will also have a panel discussion
2. *Deep tech conclave*: It will be an event consisting of speakers and panels discussing various Deep Technology like AR/VR, Artificial Intelligence, Blockchain, robotics, Advance material, or quantum computing and how these fields are disrupting the industry and startup world.
3. *Disruption Dilemma Conclave*: A Panel discussion on the theme - Disruption Dilemma
*IdeaStorm* - B-Plan Competition (Prizes worth Rs. 2.5L): It is an annual b-plan competition. If you have an idea that can change the future of business, then this the right platform to showcase your talent.
*Software Productathon (Prizes worth Rs. 2L)*: It is an offline competition in which Coders, Developers, Designers, Innovators, and Creators meet, develop, and compete in product prototyping competition in an intense 36 hours coding.
*Hardware Productathon (Prizes worth Rs. 1.5L)*: It is an offline competition to compete in hardware product prototyping in an intense 36 hours time span.
*Case Challenge (Prizes worth Rs. 1L)*: Case study competition conducted in E-Summit 2020, participants strive to develop the best solution to a real business case study within an allocated time frame.
*Investor’s Vista (Prizes worth Rs 1.5L)*: A competition to give you an investor’s perspective. The participating team will be provided with a deck of startups and asked which startup they would invest in based on the proper explanation.
*E-Conference for E-Cell members*: It is a zero-hour round table conference with an aim to create a strong network of E-Cells across India.
*Designers Meetup by Dribble*: Dribble Meetups are a chance for designers to socialize, talk shop, and foster their local design communities.
*Startup Expo (Funding opportunity of 10 Million USD)*: Startup Expo 2.0 is a marketing event for startups under the banner of E-summit’20. This event is an ideal opportunity for startups and partners wanting to market their products and grabbing the attention of potential investors or strategic partners.
*Data Enthusiasts Meetup by Kaggle*: This is a chance for data science enthusiasts to socialize and foster their local design communities, by Kaggle.
*Startup ignite*: Startup Ignite is the zonal event of E-Summit’20 IIT Roorkee, wherein IIT Roorkee expands its reach via a drive to colleges to promote entrepreneurship. iPITCH is an event in Startup ignite that will offer the participants an opportunity to step into the shoes of a CEO and other CXOs and pitch in front of investors about already existing startups or companies.
It is our great pleasure and honor to invite you for Entrepreneurship Summit 2020, IIT Roorkee.
Hope to hear from you soon.

Thanking you.
Regards

14/03/20, 8:03 pm - Anand GPT BS96: By :- Dr Sunil Karkhanis, Lung Surgeon

My nephew, who is also a lung specialist now, graduated with a master's degree, and works in *Shenzhen Hospital, China.*  He is being transferred to study *Wuhan pneumonia virus.*  He just called me and told me to tell all of my friends *NOT TO WORRY MUCH ABOUT CORONA VIRUS* : 
If you have a runny nose and sputum when you have a cold, you cannot be a patient of coronavirus pneumonia, because *coronavirus pneumonia is a dry cough without runny nose*. This is the simplest way to identify.

Please tell your friends that if you know more about medical knowledge about this virus, you will have more *awareness of identification and prevention.* 

 This time, the *Wuhan virus is not heat-resistant and will be killed at a temperature of 30-35 degrees*.

 Therefore, *drink more hot water.* You can tell your friends and relatives to drink more hot water to prevent it. *Go under the  Sun for a long time*. It has been cold season recently, and *drinking hot water is also very comfortable. It is not a cure but is a good prevention for the body. Drinking warm water is effective for mostly all viruses*. Try not to drink ice. remember that.

Doctor's advice about coronavirus:

1. It is *pretty large in size* (cell is about *400-500nm diameter*), so *any normal mask (not just the  N95 feature) should be able to filter it out*. However, when someone who's infected sneezes in front of you, it will take a great 3 meters (about 10 feet) before it drops to the ground and is *no longer airborne*. 

2. When the virus drops *on metal surface, it will live for at least 12 hours.* 
So remember if you come in contact with any metal surface, *wash your hands with soap thoroughly. Don't depend on the sanitizers.* 

3. The virus can remain active *on fabric for 6-12 hours*. 
Normal *laundry detergent should kill the virus*. 
For winter clothing that does not require daily washing, you can *put it out under the sun for 4 hours to kill the virus.* 


About the *symptoms of the pneumonia caused by Coronavirus*:

1. It will *first infect the throat, so the throat will have the dry sore throat feeling which will last for 3 to 4 days*

2. Then the virus will blend into the nasal fluid and drips into the trachea and *enter the lungs, causing pneumonia*. This process will *take 5 to 6 days*.    

3. With pneumonia, comes *high fever and difficulty in breathing*. The *nasal congestion* is not like the normal kind. You will feel like *you are drowning in water. It's important to seek immediate medical attention* if you feel like this. 

About *prevention*:

1. The most common way of getting infected is *by touching things in public*, so *you must wash your hands frequently*. The virus can only live on your hands for *5-10 minutes*, but a lot of damage can happen in those 5-10 mins (you may rub your eyes or pick your nose unwittingly).

2. Aside from washing your hands frequently, *you can gargle with Betadine Sore Throat Gargle* to eliminate or minimize the germs *while they are still in your throat (before dripping down to your lungs).* 

 *take extra care and drink plenty of water.*

India 

Week 1 - 3

Week 3 - 105

Next two weeks are crucial for India.
If we take adequate precaution and break the chain then we can tide the Corona virus Outbreak else we have a big problem in hand especially for the elderly population
So far so good. India has done well so far in its fight to contain Corona Virus. Now we are in stage 3 in which Virus spreads through social contacts & in social gatherings. This is most critical stage & number of confirmed cases spread exponentially everyday like what happened in Italy between last week of February & second week of March. From 300 to 10,000. If India is not able to manage this stage for next 3 to 4 weeks then we could have confirmed cases not in Thousands but in Lakhs. This next one month is crucial. That is why most events & public gatherings have been closed till 15th April.

Just because schools are closed avoid getting that compulsive travel & Holiday bug. Holidays will come next year too why try your luck with Corona specially with children. Marriage functions, Birthday parties etc can wait. Don’t try your luck & that bravado that nothing will happen to me. Next 30 days will be most crucial in medical History of India. Take all precautions while at home & while outside for any important work. Precaution is not panic.

Be a responsible citizen by following & educating others to remain careful for next one month.

*#CoronaVirus*

हमारी भागदौड़ भरी जिंदगी में कई कहानियाँ अक्सर दबकर रह जाती हैं, या कुछ लोगों तक ही सीमित रह जाती हैं। पर लॉकडाउन के कारण अब जब इस भागदौड़ से जिंदगी को थोड़ा आराम मिला है तो हम आपको उन कहानियों को व्यक्त करने का एक अवसर देना चाहते हैं।

👉🏻The NEO Foundation presents to you the *National Engineering Olympiad 3.0* which is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase their aptitude skills and represent themselves at the national level. 

Register now!!!
https://www.nationalolympiad.org/neo/register.php?a=713&c=1203

*When, Where, How?*

*THE ROUNDS:*
In the same manner, as the previous two editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

👉🏻*Round 1:* The online aptitude Exam. 60 min, 60 questions. Dates are 18th & 19th April 2020. The exam can be given anytime during the 48 hours from your mobile or laptop.

👉🏻*Round 2:* Telephonic interview. The telephonic interview will be conducted by our experts. 

*NOTE- You can participate in both the rounds online from your place. There is no physical location you need to be present.*

*THE REWARDS:* 

*#For top performers-*
🔘Top 5 of each year & branch will be invited for National Leadership Program by National Olympiad.
🔘Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded with medal of excellence.
🔘Top 50 of each year & branch will be awarded with certificate of excellence.

#*For all participants-*
🔘Guarenteed summer internship for all participants at partner organisations.
🔘A national level participation certificate 
🔘Upto 15 Lacs of scholarships in courses.

_Hurry up! Registrations started today!_
The clock is ticking…
Visit https://www.nationalolympiad.org/neo/register.php?a=713&c=1203

0832 0917 0950 are left

15/04/20, 9:28 pm - Kartik GPT BS81: A very simple but confusing puzzle.

A lady buys grocery worth Rs.350 from a shop. (shopkeeper selling the goods with zero profit)

The lady gives him 2000 rs note. The shopkeeper gets the change from next shop, keeps 350 for himself and returns Rs.1650 to d lady.

Later the shopkeeper of the next shop comes with the Rs.2000 note saying "duplicate" and takes his money back.
"How much LOSS did the shopkeeper face ?"

A. 350
B. 1650
C. 2350
D. 3650
E. 4000
F. Other(Specify Amount)
Simple yet confusing n challenging.

15/04/20, 9:43 pm - Amit Srivastava  GPT BS115: Suppose, Thirty one students were invited for the interviews. After greeting all 31 of them, the main
organizer remarked that I’ve no doubt about your intelligence, but it would be necessary to run a final
test to check whether all students are indeed “dedicated” enough to get the wild card entry into the
interviews as they claimed to be.
Basis of the test: He said that each student would get a hat of some color that he would place on each
student’s head. Each student would be allowed to look around (thus everyone would see the hats of all
other students except his/her own), but no communication of any sort would be allowed. After a
while, the organizer would ring a bell and if any student had deduced the color of his or her hat, they
should raise their hand. The organiser would ring a bell as many times as necessary. As the organizer
knows the color of all the hats, he also knows when each student should raise his/ her hand (if the
student is dedicated enough). This was the essence of the test.
At this stage organizer asked the participants whether there were any questions. One student raised his
hand and asked whether it was possible to pass the test i.e to correctly guess the color of the hat and
prove that he is dedicated! The organiser replied that he had selected the colors of all the hats in such
a way that every student should be able to deduce the color of his/ her hat.
As this was the only question, the test started. The organizer placed the hat on the head of all the
students and waited for a while, so that everyone had a chance to look around. After a few minutes, he
rang the bell for the first time. At this moment, four students raised their hand. When he rang the bell
for the second time, all the students with the red hat raised their hand. When he rang the bell for the
third time, no one raised their hand. When he rang the bell for the fourth time, at least one student
raised his hand. Soon afterwards, he rang the bell again, the student who asked the only question
before the commencement of the test raised his hand together with his girlfriend and some other
students- he and his girlfriend had hats of different colors. At this stage there were still some students
who didn’t raise their hand. Assuming that all the students were truly “dedicated” (so everyone was
raising the hand at the right time), how many times did the organiser ring the bell?

17/05/20, 12:13 am - Devansh GT: Haa
17/05/20, 12:19 am - Rishabh PI: Umm, so the meeting didn't go in our favour (atleast not as much as we expected).

A brief summary:
1. All the professors were against the idea (rather strictly opposed) the minimum 7 sgpa criteria. 
2. The cgpa/sgpa scored in the previous semesters would not be taken into consideration since they have no relevance what-so-ever with the current (or running) semester, so whatever grading would be done would be based on whatever evaluations we have already have.
3. They strongly rejected the proposition of giving 100% in ETE to all the students and reducing it's weightage to 20%, and adjusting the remaining 80% among the rest of the evaluation. ( one of the professors even commented that 'full marks for all the students would be a dream come true. So a big no.' 
4. Since ETEs would not be conductes, the MTEs would have major weightage in the evaluation. The professors (specifically Prof. S.K. Ghosh) were against giving an additional 20 marks to enhance the overall MTE score (as proposed by Prof. Samadhya), with the reasoning that 'we can not give gifts to the students'. 
5. The CWS evaluation which took place before the MTE would have significant weightage.
6. E-Learning would also have some weightage.


We tried to haggle the % weightage of these evaluations. The proposed MTE weightage was 50% by the professors, 25% CWS (including the tutorial submission) and 25% E-Learning. At the end of the discussion, the weightage decided are as follows: MTE 40 - 50%; E-Learning 0 - 10%; CWS (tutorials, Attendance Quiz etc) - 40 - 50%.

Such a conclusion was made keeping the following points in mind -
1. Usually, students are very casual with the MTEs and tend to improve their scores through ETE. Thus, given that we are not having ETEs, MTE is the only physical (pen/paper) evaluation conducted so it needs to have a significant weightage.
2. Not everyone has access to good internet connection, and even if they do, most of the students are occupied with internships, so having a weightage in the range 0 to 10% makes sense. 
3. CWS is a section where we would have the chance to talk to our professors, explain our situation if need be, and possibly get our marks changed. So, significant weightage has been given to this as well.

This was the best we could make them settle on. 

This would further be discussed by the professors and then sent to the chairman faculty senate. 

The professors of our department are not supportive of the students it seems, hopefully the other branches would have better and student-favouring conclusions.

The inputs from all the departments would be taken into consideration by the faculty senate and then the final decision would be taken. Hence, it doesn't necessarily means that the conclusions of this meeting would be implemented. 


If anyone has any other good suggestions given the above points, please let us know. We'll send the proposition to HoD sir.

02/06/20, 12:50 am - Kanak GPT: Dear students,
 
About us
Amrit Skills Pvt. Ltd. is one of India’s leading assessment companies that helps organizations, governments and institutions measure and identify talent. Since its inception, Amrit is deeply involved in evaluating & assessing the skills imparted under various training schemes in the country. Under the skill development program run by the central government, they are certified as an assessment body by Textile committee, Ministry of Textiles and NSDC, Ministry of Skill Development & Entrepreneurship and the Gems and Jewellery Sector. The inspiration and spirit behind the enterprise is to contribute in making India a Global Skill capital by developing a merit driven labour market where everyone has the access to talent and opportunity.
 
 
They require a content creation team for their Marketing division. The team will be allotted work for:

website content

blogs

case studies

newsletter

 
They also require graphic content creators for E-posters, video editing etc. for digital marketing.
 
Initially the internship will be for a month but can be renewed on the basis of quality of work.
 
Interested students should send their resume and expression of interest (optional) to vinita@amritskills.com.

19/06/20, 8:54 pm - Amit Yadav GPT: Pros and Cons of taking S grade:-
1. Many foreign Universities are not accepting the students with S grade are not accepting applications for admission to them, as you may find in the link below.
2. Taking S grade may benefit you this semester, but in a long run, it may not sound well.
For example, if someone scored 8.2 in first SEM, and this sem, his CG is 10,10,9,8,8,7 and suppose his CG for the all 6 next semesters be 7.5, then:
Case 1. If he chooses S grade for 8, 8 and 7, his overall CG at the end would be
{8.2(21) + (10*4 + 10*4 + 9*4) + 7.5(125)} / 158
(Because the total credits are 170 and he has dropped three courses of 4 credits each)
So the CG = 7.75

Case 2. If he doesn't take S grade in any subject, then the CG would be
{8.2(21) + (10*4 + 10*4 + 9*4 + 8*4 + 8*4 + 7*4) + 7.5(125)} / 170
Which is also 7.75
Even if you consider the extreme case, then the max change at the end of 4th year in CG would be .25

And further it may not sound nice for an interview because the interviewer would only be seeing an "S" grade, he won't be knowing whether  the grade behind that S is 7 or 5. So that depends upon you, whether you choose a .25 difference with an S grade or not.

3. In the above example, the AVG CG for the rest of the semesters was assumed to be 7.5
If it goes less than that, then taking S grade won't be beneficial at all, but if it goes more than that, then taking S grade would be fruitful. Further it also depends upon what your present CG is. 


So overall it's totally up to you. You do some calculations and figure out what is best for you. Further, it's a humble request that you all must discuss all this with your parents. The motive of this entire note was to give you an idea of long term pros and cons of S grade.

Civil CRs and BRs

This internship is for coding enthusiasts, inclined towards making a career in front end development. The project in hand is an ecommerce web and a mobile application for one of the leading exhibition organisers in India. The internship will focus on getting hands on experience into various front end tools as well as mobile app building. We are looking for self motivated learners who love coding :)

Date of Beginning: 20th July
Time: 10 am - 6 pm, 5 days a week
Duration: 6 months
Tech Stack: Angular 7, Javascript, Typescript, HTML/CSS/JQuery, MySQL, Dotnet, Ionic

Openings: 6

Selected intern's day-to-day responsibilities include:
1. Developing modules using Angular 7/8
2. Assisting in reproducing and solving bugs
3. Assisting in developing state-of-art UI
4. Learning Ionic in the training given

Pre-requisites:
1. Students who have a good base in Angular 7
2. Excellent problem solving skills in Data Structures and Algorithms
3. Can commit for at least 4-6 months 

Stipend:
3k a month after performance evaluation for initial 15 days (no stipend then)

Application Process:
1. Interested students can send us their resumes on lisha@swabhavtechlabs.com along with a link to your github account if you have projects to show.
3. A small 15 mcq based online test (30 min long) .. language independent to test logic and critical thinking.
4. Small one day assignment to test knowledge in Angular.
5. Letter of internship signing and commencement

आइंस्टीन के ड्राइवर ने एक बार आइंस्टीन से कहा--"सर, मैंने हर बैठक में आपके द्वारा दिए गए हर भाषण को याद किया है।"

 आइंस्टीन हैरान !!!

उन्होंने कहा- "ठीक है, अगले आयोजक मुझे नहीं जानते।आप मेरे स्थान पर वहां बोलिए और मैं ड्राइवर बनूंगा।

ऐसा ही हुआ, बैठक में अगले दिन ड्राइवर मंच पर चढ़ गया।और भाषण देने लगा...

उपस्थित विद्वानों ने जोर-शोर से तालियां बजाईं।

उस समय एक प्रोफेसर ने ड्राइवर से पूछा - "सर, क्या आप उस सापेक्षता की परिभाषा को फिर से समझा सकते हैं ?"

असली आइंस्टीन ने देखा बड़ा खतरा !!! 

इस बार वाहन चालक पकड़ा जाएगा। लेकिन ड्राइवर का जवाब सुनकर वे हैरान रह गए...

मेरे ड्राइवर से पूछिए,---वह आपको समझाएगा ।"

नोट :  "यदि आप बुद्धिमान लोगों के साथ चलते हैं, तो आप भी बुद्धिमान बनेंगे और मूर्खों के साथ ही सदा उठेंगे-बैठेंगे तो आपका मानसिक तथा बुद्धिमता का स्तर और सोच भी उन्हीं की भांति हो जाएगी..!!!"

30/07/20, 9:10 am - Saksham Chem.: *Very important decision Government*

New Education Policy 2020 is announced

1. 10+2 board structure is   dropped
2. New school structure will be 5+3+3+4
3. Upto 5 pre school, 6 to 8 Mid School, 8 to 11 High School , 12 onwards Graduation
4. Any Degree will be 4 years
5. 6th std onwards vocational courses available
6. From 8th to 11 students can choose subjects 
7. All graduation course will have major and minor
Example - science student can have Physics as Major and Music as minor also. Any combination he can choose
8. All higher education will be governed by only one authority. 
9. UGC AICTE will be merged.
10. All University government, private, Open, Deemed, Vocational etc will have same grading and other rules.
11. New Teacher Training board will be setup for all kinds of teachers in country, no state can change
12. Same level of Accreditation to any collage , based on its rating collage will get autonomous rights and funds.
13. New Basic learning program will be created by government for parents to teach children upto 3 years in home and for pre school 3 to 6
14. Multiple entry and exit from any course 
15. Credit system for graduation for each year student will get some credits which he can utilize if he takes break in course and come back again to complete course
16. All schools exams will be semester wise twise a year
17. The syllabus will be reduced to core knowledge of any subject only
18. More focus on student practical and application knowledge
19. For any graduation course if student complete only one year he will get a basic certificate, if he complete two years then he will get Diploma certificate and if he complete full course then he will get degree certificate. So no year of any student will ve vested if he break the course in between.
20.All the graduation course feed of all Universities will be govern by single authority with capping on each course.

Now we can hope our education system will be at par with moder countries and future of our children will be bright.
